The Senate will engage the Executive arm of government over the non-release of any amount from the N45 billion approved for the Presidential Committee on Northeast Initiatives (PCNI) in the 2018 budget. The chairman of the Senate Committee on Special Duties, Abdulaziz Nyako (ADC, Adamawa), said this during an oversight visit to the PCNI headquarters in Abuja yesterday. Tanimu is an Online Editor with Africa's Largest TV Network. Produces when not on Social media.